bid(uint256).details: Bids on an open auction, completing the auction and transferring      ownership of the NFT if enough Ether has been supplied

params._tokenId: - ID of token to bid on

cancelAuction(uint256).details: Cancels an auction that hasn't been won yet     Returns the token to its original owner

constructor.details: Constructor creates a reference to the NFT ownership contract      and verifies the contract owner cut is within the valid range

params._ownerCut: - percentage cut the contract owner takes on each auction,       must be between 0-10,000 (basis points)
params._tokenContractAddress: - address of a deployed contract implementing       the ERC721 interface

params._duration: - Length of time (in seconds) to move between the         starting price and the ending price
params._endingPrice: - Final price (in wei) the auction can reach
params._seller: - The listed seller for the auction (the token owner         can set someone else as the seller/beneficiary)
params._startingPrice: - Starting price (in wei) at beginning of auction
params._tokenId: - ID of token to auction, sender must be its owner

getAuction(uint256).details: Returns the data for an auction

params._tokenId: - ID of the token being auction

getCurrentPrice(uint256).details: Returns the current price of an auction

params._tokenId: - ID of the token on auction
